# Project 2 â€” Bathymetry Visualization of Turkish Waters

Visualized ocean depth across Turkey's three sea basins (Black Sea, Aegean, 
and Mediterranean) using GEBCO 2025 gridded bathymetry data.

## What This Project Demonstrates
- Working with raster/GeoTIFF data in QGIS
- Applying professional depth color ramps using PyQGIS
- Overlaying vector EEZ boundaries on raster data
- Automated map layout and export with Python

## Tools Used
- QGIS
- Python (PyQGIS)

## Data Sources
- [GEBCO 2025 Gridded Bathymetry](https://download.gebco.net)
- [Marine Regions World EEZ v12](https://www.marineregions.org)

## Key Observations
- The Black Sea has a maximum depth of ~2,200m with a distinct deep basin
- The Aegean is significantly shallower with complex underwater terrain
- The Eastern Mediterranean reaches depths of ~4,500m

